//🔹 What is a Session?
// A session stores user data on the server so that the user remains logged in across multiple requests/pages.
//When a user logs in successfully, you store some information in req.session.

//🔹 Example Flow

//1️⃣ User logs in
//2️⃣ Server verifies email & password
//3️⃣ Session is created

Session;
{
  userId: 5;
  role: "admin";
}

//4️⃣ Browser receives session cookie

//5️⃣ Every request will automatically send that cookie.


//hbs
//Handlebars are template engine for nodejs.
It helps you generate dynamic HTML pages using backend data.

Instead of writing static HTML like:

<h1>Hello User</h1>

You can make it dynamic:

<h1>Hello {{name}}</h1>



FLASH
// Success example
req.flash("success", "Login successful! Welcome back.");
res.redirect("/freeze-feast/dashboard");

// Error example
req.flash("error", "Invalid credentials. Try again.");
res.redirect("/freeze-feast/login");

// Info / Warning
req.flash("info", "Your session will expire soon.");
req.flash("warning", "Please verify your email.");
res.redirect("/somewhere");

Key rule: Always redirect after setting flash — never render. Flash reads on the next request, so render won't show it.